.SH RULE-ENGINE

The
.B rule-engine
module provides natural-language firewall management within the
.B one-click
toolkit.

.PP
It allows administrators to construct firewall rules using human-readable syntax,
which are automatically translated into valid commands for the active firewall backend.

Supported backends include:

.IP \(bu 2
.B iptables / ip6tables

.IP \(bu 2
.B nftables

.PP
The rule-engine combines natural language parsing with a transactional
execution model designed to prevent accidental lockouts.

.PP
Firewall changes are applied using a staged commit process with automatic rollback protection.
A
.B 10-second verification timer
ensures that changes can be automatically reverted if confirmation is not received.

.SH RULE-ENGINE FEATURES

.IP \(bu 2
Human-readable firewall rule parsing

.IP \(bu 2
Support for TCP, UDP, ICMP, and multiport rules

.IP \(bu 2
Source and destination filtering using IPv4, IPv6, and CIDR ranges

.IP \(bu 2
Service-name to port mapping (e.g., ssh → 22)

.IP \(bu 2
Automatic detection of the firewall backend

.IP \(bu 2
Natural language and raw command chaining

.IP \(bu 2
Firewall rule alias system for IP groups

.IP \(bu 2
Sensitive port protection

.IP \(bu 2
Dry-run preview mode (--dry-run)

.IP \(bu 2
Audit mode for rule inspection

.IP \(bu 2
Full firewall backup and restore management

.IP \(bu 2
Transactional commit system with rollback protection

